**Product Requirements Document: “NoCap” (v1.0)**  
**1\. Overview & Vision**

"NoCap" is an intelligent, minimalist financial advisor designed to help users effortlessly track and, more importantly, *understand* their spending habits. In a market of cluttered and complex financial apps, our vision is to provide clarity and insight through a beautiful, intuitive interface. We are moving beyond simple data logging to become a proactive partner in our users' financial wellness.  
This document outlines the requirements for the initial release (V1) of the mobile application.  
**2\. Goals & Success Metrics**

Our primary goal is to build an app that users love and find indispensable for managing their daily finances.

* **Product Goals:**  
  * Establish a core user base that is highly engaged.  
  * Deliver a "wow" experience through design and insightful features.  
* **Success Metrics (First 3 Months):**  
  * **Engagement:** Achieve a Daily Active Users (DAU) count of 1,000+.  
  * **Retention:** D30 Retention Rate \> 20%.  
  * **Feature Adoption:** \>30% of new users try the AI Scan feature at least once.  
  * **Business:** Achieve a Free-to-Paid Conversion Rate of \>2%.

**3\. Target Audience**

Design-conscious individuals aged 20-35 who are comfortable with technology and want to be more mindful of their spending without the hassle of complex spreadsheets or traditional budgeting apps. They value simplicity, aesthetics, and actionable insights over granular control.  
**4\. Proposed Tech Stack & Architecture**

The proposed stack is modern, scalable, and leverages the best of the Bolt.new ecosystem.

* **Frontend:** **Bolt.new** (To build the core application interface).  
* **Mobile Deployment:** **Expo.dev** (To manage the build and deployment process for iOS and Android).  
* **Backend & Database:** **Supabase** (For user authentication, database, and image storage).  
* **Monetization:** **RevenueCat** (To manage subscriptions and the paywall).  
* **AI Image Recognition:** A third-party API (e.g., Google Cloud Vision, Amazon Rekognition, or a specialized receipt OCR API) integrated via a Supabase Edge Function.

**Important Architectural Note: Cloud vs. Local Storage**

To enable critical features like cross-device sync, secure data backup (if a user loses their phone), **we will use Supabase as the single source of truth for user data.**

* **Decision:** We will proceed with a cloud-based architecture.  
* **Justification:** The value provided by secure cloud sync and backup far outweighs the marketing angle of a "local-only" app, which is prone to complete data loss. We will be transparent about this in our privacy policy, emphasizing that user data is securely stored via Supabase and never shared or sold.

* **Primary Font:** SF Compact Rounded.  
* **Interactions:** Animations should be smooth, purposeful, and delightful (e.g., the number count-up animation). They should feel responsive and high-quality.  
* **Color Palette:** Dominated by blacks, dark grays, and a primary accent color (e.g., the orange/red in the chart) for highlighting data. Warning colors (yellow, red) will be used for budget alerts.

**6\. Core Features (V1)**

**6.1. The Home "Advisor" Screen**

This is the central hub of the app. It provides an at-a-glance summary and insight.

This is the central hub of the app. It provides an at-a-glance summary, insight, and serves as the entry point for all core actions.

* **User Story 1: View Spending Overview (Revised & Finalized)**  
  1. **As a user,** I want to see my spending for the selected time period displayed as a large, visually striking number surrounded by a "Budget Ring" that shows my progress against my budget.  
* **Acceptance Criteria:**  
  1. **Central Display:** The screen's focal point will be the numerical spending value (e.g., `$50.00`) and the surrounding Budget Ring.  
  2. **Numerical Styling:**  
     * The font size of the number will be significantly increased to be the dominant visual element.  
     * The font weight for the main dollar value will be **Bold** or **Semibold**.  
     * To create a clear typographic hierarchy, the cents value (e.g., `.00`) will be styled with a **Regular or Light font weight** and a slightly smaller font size.  
  3. **The Budget Ring:**  
     * A circular ring will encircle the primary number.  
     * This ring will fill up proportionally as spending increases towards the set budget for the selected time period (Today/Month).  
     * The ring's color will be neutral (e.g., a light gray or off-white) by default.  
  4. **Color Logic (Applied to both Number and Ring):**  
     * `< 80%` of Budget: Neutral color (White/Light Gray).  
     * `80% - 99.9%`: Warning color (Muted Yellow).  
     * `≥ 100%`: Exceeded color (Muted Red).  
  5. **Interaction:** The user can swipe left/right on the number/ring area to cycle through "Today," and "This Month" views. This transition must be animated smoothly (e.g., a cross-fade).  
* **User Story 2: Interact with Key Metrics**  
  * **As a user,** I want to be able to swipe horizontally on the "today" spending number to see my total spending for "this month."  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * Swiping left/right on the main number cycles the view between Today \-\> This Month \-\> Today.  
    * The interaction is smooth and responsive.  
* **User Story 3: Log an Expense Manually**  
  * **As a user,** I want to single-tap anywhere on the home screen to quickly log a new expense.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * A single tap triggers a pop-up/modal for expense entry.  
    * The pop-up contains fields for: Item Name (Text), Amount ($), Category (Dropdown), Date (Defaults to today), Recurrence (Optional: None, Weekly, Monthly).  
    * Upon saving, the home screen's relevant number animates, counting up to the new total.  
* **User Story 4: Set a Budget**  
  * **As a user,** I want to double-tap anywhere on the home screen to set or adjust my budget.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * A double tap triggers a pop-up for budget entry.  
    * The user can set a Daily Budget and/or a Monthly Budget.  
    * The home screen number (today/month) changes color based on proximity to the set budget:  
      * \< 80%: Neutral color (White)  
      * 80% \- 99.9%: Warning color (Yellow)  
      * ≥ 100%: Exceeded color (Red)  
* **User Story (NEW): Access AI Logging**  
  * **As a user,** I want to see a **minimalist camera icon in the top-right corner of the screen** so I can quickly access the AI scanning feature.  
* **User Story (NEW): Access Account Settings**  
  * **As a user,** I want to see a **minimalist gear icon in the top-left corner of the screen** so I can easily access my account information and app settings.

**6.2. Transactions Panel**

A simple, clean interface for reviewing and managing past spending, **accessible directly from the Home Screen.**

* **User Story 5: Review and Manage Transactions**  
  * **As a user,** I want to **swipe up from the bottom of the Home Screen** to reveal a panel containing my transaction history.  
  * **As a user,** I want to be able to filter this list by a Date Range and/or by Category.  
  * **As a user,** I want to tap on any transaction to easily edit or delete it.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * **The text area and chevron icon at the bottom of the Home Screen (“Transactions”) acts as a "handle" for the history panel.**  
    * **A short upward drag reveals a "peek" of the transaction list. A full swipe up expands the panel to cover most of the screen.**  
    * The list is clean and legible. Each entry shows Item Name, Amount, and Date.  
    * Filter controls are intuitive and allow for single or combined filtering.  
    * Editing a transaction opens a view with the pre-filled data, which can then be modified and saved.

**6.3. AI-Powered Expense Logging**

The "killer feature" of the premium tier, **initiated from the Home Screen.**

* **User Story 6: Log an Expense with AI**  
  * **As a user,** I want to tap the **camera icon in the top-right of the Home Screen** to use my camera to take a photo of an item or a receipt.  
  * **As a user,** I want the app to use AI to analyze the photo and automatically pre-fill the expense details (Item Name, Amount).  
  * **As a user,** I want to be able to review and complete the remaining fields (e.g., category) before confirming and saving the expense.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * A clear CTA for the AI Scan is present.  
    * The camera interface is simple.  
    * After photo analysis, the expense logging pop-up appears with the AI-detected fields pre-filled.  
    * The user must manually confirm the entry before it is saved.

**6.4. Onboarding Flow**

**A personalized, benefit-driven setup experience designed to maximize user excitement, trust, and long-term engagement.**

* **User Story 7: Experience a Welcoming Onboarding**  
  * **As a new user,** I want to be taken through a brief (3-4 screen) onboarding flow that explains the app's core value and gets me excited to start.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * **Screen 1: Welcome.** A simple, beautiful welcome screen with the app's name.  
    * **Screen 2: Core Value.** A quick, animated demonstration of the home screen, showing how to log an expense and see the chart. Text: “No cap track and understand your spending, instantly.”  
    * **Screen 3: Introduce Tiers.** Clearly present the Free vs. "Pro" tier. "Start for free, or unlock unlimited AI expense scanning with Pro." Include a "Continue" button. This is *not* the paywall, just an introduction.  
    * **Screen 4: Notifications & Final Setup.**  
      * This screen first asks for notification permission contextually: "Get timely alerts when you're approaching your budget. Allow notifications?" \[Allow/Don't Allow buttons\].  
      * After the user chooses, the screen shows a brief (2-3 second) animation with a loading indicator.  
      * **Text:** Completing your dashboard...  
      * Upon completion, the user lands on the fully functional Home Screen.

**6.5. Account & Settings Screen**

This screen serves as the central location for users to manage their account, subscription, and preferences. It is accessed by tapping the gear icon on the Home Screen. The screen should be composed of a simple list of options.

* **User Story 8: Manage Subscription and Profile**  
  * **As a user,** I want to see my account details (e.g., the email I signed up with) and my current subscription status ("Free" or "Pro").  
  * **As a Pro user,** I want a clear way to manage my subscription (which will link to the native iOS/Android subscription management page).  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * The screen displays the user's email address.  
    * A "Subscription" or "Manage Plan" cell clearly indicates the current tier.  
    * Tapping this cell for a Pro user will open the appropriate subscription management interface provided by the RevenueCat SDK / OS.  
* **User Story 9: Control App Preferences**  
  * **As a user,** I want to be able to enable or disable app notifications.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * A "Notifications" option is present with a simple toggle switch (On/Off).  
* **User Story 10: Perform Account Actions**  
  * **As a user,** I want a clear and obvious way to Log Out of my account.  
  * **As a user,** I want the ability to permanently Delete My Account and all associated data from the app.  
  * **Acceptance Criteria:**  
    * A "Log Out" button is present. Tapping it will prompt a confirmation before logging the user out.  
    * A "Delete Account" button is present, likely styled in a red/destructive color. Tapping it will trigger a confirmation modal that clearly states the action is irreversible before proceeding with account deletion via Supabase.

**7\. Monetization Model: Freemium**

* **Free Tier:**  
  * Unlimited manual expense tracking.  
  * Full access to history and filtering.  
  * Full budgeting functionality.  
* **Premium Tier ("Pro"):**  
  * Includes all Free features.  
  * **Unlocks Unlimited AI-powered expense scanning.**  
* **Paywall Flow:**  
  * All users receive **3 free uses** of the AI Scan feature.  
  * A counter can subtly show remaining free uses (e.g., "2 scans left").  
  * On the **4th attempt** to use the AI Scan, the **RevenueCat Paywall Builder** is triggered.  
  * The paywall will be elegantly designed, reinforcing the value proposition: "Save time. Never forget an expense. Unlock unlimited AI scanning with Pro."

**8\. Out of Scope for V1**

To ensure a focused and timely launch, the following features will **not** be included in V1:

* Multi-currency support.  
* Advanced analytics dashboards or custom reports.  
* Connecting to bank accounts for automatic transaction import.  
* Shared budgets or social features.  
* A web or tablet version of the app.  
* The full "Digest" screen (the home screen insight is the V1 implementation).
